summary: This is a letter from Expedia, Inc. to an FBI Special Agent dated March 17, 2020, responding to a subpoena dated January 27, 2020. Expedia states that after conducting a diligent search, they were unable to locate any responsive records related to the subpoena in the Epstein case.

persons.name: Michelle Velasquez
persons.context: Michelle Velasquez signed the letter on behalf of Expedia, Inc. as the paralegal responding to the FBI subpoena.

events.title: FBI Subpoena Issued to Expedia
events.description: The FBI issued a subpoena to Expedia, Inc. as part of the Epstein investigation, requesting records.

events.title: Expedia's Response to Subpoena
events.description: Expedia, Inc. responded to the FBI subpoena, stating that after a diligent search, they were unable to locate any responsive records.

keyFacts: The FBI issued a subpoena to Expedia, Inc. on January 27, 2020, as part of the Epstein investigation.
Expedia conducted a reasonable and diligent search for responsive records but was unable to locate any.
The response was sent via email on March 17, 2020, by Michelle Velasquez, a paralegal at Expedia.
This document indicates the FBI was seeking travel-related records from Expedia in connection with the Epstein case.
The subpoena and response are part of the broader investigation into Epstein's activities and associates.
